			     DNSSEC-Tools
			Is your domain secure?


This directory contains documentation for the validator.

NOTE: manual pages (*.1, *.3) are autogenerated from the pod pages.
      DO NOT EDIT THE MANUAL PAGES, YOUR CHANGES WILL BE LOST.

* libval.pod, libval.3
	Man page for the interfaces exported by the core validation library namely,
	val_resolve_and_check(), 
	val_free_result_chain(), val_create_context(), val_free_context(), 
	switch_effective_policy(), p_val_error().

* val_gethostbyname.pod, val_gethostbyname.3
	Man page for the val_gethostbyname(),
	val_x_gethostbyname(), val_get_hostent_dnssec_status(),
	val_duphostent() and val_freehostent() functions of the
	validator API.

* val_getaddrinfo.pod, val_getaddrinfo.3
	Man page for the val_getaddrinfo(),
	val_x_getaddrinfo(), val_get_addrinfo_dnssec_status(),
	val_dupaddrinfo() and val_freeaddrinfo() functions of the
	validator API.

* val_query.pod, val_query.3
	Man page for the val_query() and val_x_query()
	functions of the validator API.

* validate.pod, validate.3
	Man page for the apps/validate utility

*validator_api.xml
	The XML source for draft-hayatnagarkar-dnsext-validator-api, 
	which also describes the interface for libval 
	The txt version of the draft can be generated using the
	xml2rfc utility present at http://xml.resource.org/

*implementation-notes-libval
	Contains information on some of the design choices and the 
	implementation of the libval library.

*implementation-notes-libsres
	Contains information on some of the design choices and the 
	implementation of the libsres library.
